> * Drug Wilfred with Cat
[Comment recorded]

> EAST

Scriptorium
The Scriptorium---where brothers create the illuminated manuscripts that are a primary source of priory income---smells of ink, manuscripts, and woodsmoke. High windows admit the cool morning light the season allows, and a modest fire burns in the fireplace, keeping the manuscripts dry despite the sea air. 

The large central table is covered with the materials of the illuminator's art as well as a sample of their work. 

The Cloister is out to west; the Library is east, through the closed door.

Brother Wilfred sits at the table, close to the fireplace.

Brother Wilfred notices the orange cat in your arms. "Hello", he says to her. "Making new friends, are we?"

> ASK WILFRED ABOUT PAX
His eyes glisten. "Forgive an old brother, but that cat has become very dear to me. I was the one who named her---'Pax', for the peace she brings to these old halls."

> GIVE PAX TO WILFRED

A tender smile comes to Brother Wilfred's lined face. "Ah", he murmurs to Pax, "come to check on an old man?" Pax leaps onto his lap and settles there. His hand moves to stroke her, and his eyes grow heavier almost at once.

> X WILFRED
Brother Wilfred, the librarian, is the most venerated of the brethren, well over seventy. He's lean and wiry, with wisps of white hair shooting in all directions from his head. His habit has bits of orange fluff or fur on it.

He currently has Pax on his lap.

As Pax rests in his lap, Brother Wilfred begins to snore.


                                                         
                       The sleepy like to make excuses.  
                                                         
